The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Bhutia brace in India victory

OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

New Delhi: Skipper Bhaichung Bhutia struck two goals in the second half as India outplayed Second Division Portuguese side Recreativo Agueda 3-0 in their second tour match at Aguedas Municipal Stadium on Sunday. 

According to Information received here, Bhutia displayed vintage form after being put into the second half. Chief Coach Bob Houghton started the match with Tarif Ahmed and Manjit Singh in the frontline and brought in the first team players in the second session. 

Manjit Singh put India in the lead in the 27th minute. 

After change of ends, India bolstered the lead through Bhutia in the 63rd minute. The Sikkimese striker rounded off the tally four minutes from time. 




